div.p:
               Perhaps a sound Statesmanship will prevail here in my affairs, though Mr Casey is already on his backway;

J. J. Casey lost his ministerial position with the defeat of the government led by G. B. Kerferd in August 1875. Thereafter he maintained an independent position in the Legislative Assembly between the conservative and radical parties.
                if so I shall be able to write once more with renewed hopes of life and increased means for work & prospects in a more cheerful spirit. If any expressions of mine in this or former letters (it may be my last in my fluctuating health) may be regarded by you as not right, then kindly excuse it, because I combat not merely for the continuance of my own work, but as a scientific man for a scientific position on scientific principles.
